On this page, you will need to introduce your worklog. How did you complete it? How many weeks did you take to complete the program? What did you do in those weeks?
Typically, and as a standard, a worklog is carried out over about 3 months (throughout the internship period) with weekly contents as follows:
Week 1: AWS Foundations, Networking, Security, and Hands-on Labs
Week 2: Hands-on with AWS Compute (EC2, Auto Scaling, Load Balancing), Monitoring (CloudWatch), Backup, and Storage Services (S3, FSx, Storage Gateway)
Week 3: AWS Security &amp; Database Services (IAM, Cognito, KMS, RDS, Aurora, Redshift, ElastiCache)
Week 4: AWS Data Analytics, NoSQL, and AI Lifecycle Exploration Week
Week 5: Doing task D&hellip;
Week 6: Doing task E&hellip;
Week 7: Doing task G&hellip;
Week 8: Doing task H&hellip;
Week 9: Doing task I&hellip;
